        <h1 style="text-align: center;">Quick Start Guide</h1>

        <h2>General</h2>
        <p style="border-bottom: 2px solid lightgrey; padding-bottom: 5px;">
            This application provides an intuitive visual interface for viewing and maintaining the <em>Commercial Off-The-Shelf</em> (COTS) <em>Software Inventory</em>. <br />
            Immediately below is an important note about how this application maintains referenctial integrity by virtue of <em>cascade deletion</em>, which one <br />
            must be aware of in order to enter data effectively. Following that are detailed summaries of each table contained in the database. For a <br />
            more techinical description of this application, pertinant information regarding it's maintenence, and contact information for it's author, <br />
            please see <strong>README.md</strong> located in the source-root.
        </p>

        <br />

        <h3>Cascade Deletion Map</h3>
        <p>
            Here, a map shows the deletion behavior when a <em>principal entity</em> is deleted. <br />
            If you delete an entry that other entries depended on (pointed to via FK's), <br />
            those <em>dependant entities</em> will be deleted as well to avoid holes in the database. <br />
            Likewise, if you wish to add an entry that points to a <em>principal</em> entry, make sure <br />
            that entry exists first. Guards will prevent you from adding invalid null pointers.
        </p>
